## Preventing Future Incidents

While it's important to know how to respond if your phone is stolen, prevention is always better than recovery. Make it a habit to back up your important data to <a href="https://drive.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Drive</a> or external storage. This way, even if you lose your phone, you won't lose your valuable information.

Always use a strong password or biometric lock, and enable features like 'Find My Device.' These small steps can make a big difference in keeping your phone secure.

Losing a phone is never ideal, but with tools like 'Find My Device' and CrookCatcher, you can protect your data and improve your chances of getting your device back. Proactive steps like securing your accounts and backing up your data ensure you're prepared for any situation.
